---
import BaseLayout from '../../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const description = 'A Vaelinyan time artefact that gathers light, bells, water, seasons, and the two moons into one visible pattern.';
---
<BaseLayout title="The Listening Clock" description={description}>
  <section class="page-section listening-clock-page">
    <p class="eyebrow">World · Time · Artefact</p>
    <h1>The Listening Clock</h1>
    <p class="lede">The Listening Clock does not only count. It gathers signs.</p>
    <p>Light, bell marks, water movement, the four seasonal arcs, and the two moons all pass through its face. A Timekeeper can read the clock as a pattern before reading it as a number.</p>

    <article class="clock-artefact" aria-labelledby="clock-title">
      <div class="clock-copy">
        <p class="eyebrow">Visible pattern</p>
        <h2 id="clock-title">What the clock is hearing now</h2>
        <p>The outer rings turn slowly. The inner rings answer more quickly. The two moon paths do not match each other, so the water ring is never perfectly simple.</p>
        <p class="clock-reading" id="clock-reading" aria-live="polite">The clock is listening.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="clock-shell" aria-label="A live Vaelinyan Listening Clock showing rings for seconds, minutes, hours, year, two moons, and water pull.">
        <div class="clock-halo" aria-hidden="true"></div>
        <svg class="listening-clock" viewBox="0 0 360 360" role="img" aria-labelledby="clock-svg-title clock-svg-desc">
          <title id="clock-svg-title">The Listening Clock</title>
          <desc id="clock-svg-desc">Concentric rings show the movement of the day, year, two moons, and river pull.</desc>

          <circle class="clock-back-ring" cx="180" cy="180" r="158" />
          <circle class="clock-back-ring" cx="180" cy="180" r="136" />
          <circle class="clock-back-ring" cx="180" cy="180" r="114" />
          <circle class="clock-back-ring" cx="180" cy="180" r="92" />
          <circle class="clock-back-ring" cx="180" cy="180" r="70" />
          <circle class="clock-back-ring" cx="180" cy="180" r="48" />

          <g class="ring-layer ring-year">
            <circle data-ring="year" class="clock-progress" cx="180" cy="180" r="158" pathLength="1" />
            <circle data-dot="year" class="clock-dot" r="4.5" />
          </g>
          <g class="ring-layer ring-aelun">
            <circle data-ring="aelun" class="clock-progress" cx="180" cy="180" r="136" pathLength="1" />
            <circle data-dot="aelun" class="clock-dot moon-dot" r="5.5" />
          </g>
          <g class="ring-layer ring-saelith">
            <circle data-ring="saelith" class="clock-progress" cx="180" cy="180" r="114" pathLength="1" />
            <circle data-dot="saelith" class="clock-dot moon-dot small" r="4" />
          </g>
          <g class="ring-layer ring-water">
            <circle data-ring="water" class="clock-progress" cx="180" cy="180" r="92" pathLength="1" />
            <circle data-dot="water" class="clock-dot water-dot" r="5" />
          </g>
          <g class="ring-layer ring-hour">
            <circle data-ring="hour" class="clock-progress" cx="180" cy="180" r="70" pathLength="1" />
            <circle data-dot="hour" class="clock-dot" r="4" />
          </g>
          <g class="ring-layer ring-minute">
            <circle data-ring="minute" class="clock-progress" cx="180" cy="180" r="48" pathLength="1" />
            <circle data-dot="minute" class="clock-dot" r="3.5" />
          </g>

          <circle class="clock-centre" cx="180" cy="180" r="31" />
          <text class="clock-centre-text" id="clock-centre-text" x="180" y="176" text-anchor="middle">LISTEN</text>
          <text class="clock-centre-subtext" id="clock-centre-subtext" x="180" y="196" text-anchor="middle">--:--</text>
        </svg>
      </div>
    </article>

    <article class="panel read-clock-panel" aria-labelledby="read-clock-title">
      <p class="eyebrow">How to read this</p>
      <h2 id="read-clock-title">Read the large movements first</h2>
      <div class="reading-grid">
        <section>
          <h3>Year ring</h3>
          <p>Shows the long turn through Holding, Loosening, Opening, and Returning.</p>
        </section>
        <section>
          <h3>Aelun</h3>
          <p>The larger visible moon. Common counting follows this moon most often.</p>
        </section>
        <section>
          <h3>Saelith</h3>
          <p>The smaller, older-count moon. Its path is slower and less ordinary.</p>
        </section>
        <section>
          <h3>Water</h3>
          <p>The river answers both moons. When the pulls meet, the water becomes more forceful.</p>
        </section>
        <section>
          <h3>Hour and minute</h3>
          <p>These are the quick rings. They help a Timekeeper place the local moment.</p>
        </section>
        <section>
          <h3>Centre</h3>
          <p>The centre gives a plain time so the artefact stays readable.</p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </article>

    <article class="visual-callout visual-callout-world story-callout">
      <div class="visual-callout-mark" aria-hidden="true"><span>◌</span></div>
      <div class="visual-callout-copy">
        <p class="eyebrow">Story path</p>
        <h2>The clock will belong to Lina too</h2>
        <p>One day Lina will find a clock that waits instead of hurrying. For now, this page gives the artefact a place in the world.</p>
      </div>
    </article>

    <div class="link-list">
      <a href="/world/time/">Back to Time</a>
      <a href="/world/time/two-moons/">The Two Moons</a>
      <a href="/world/time/calendar/">Calendar</a>
      <a href="/world/">Back to World</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<script>
  const TAU = Math.PI * 2;
  const CENTRE = 180;
  const RADIUS = {
    year: 158,
    aelun: 136,
    saelith: 114,
    water: 92,
    hour: 70,
    minute: 48,
  };

  const MONTHS = [
    ['Frosthold', 'Holding'],
    ['White Edge', 'Holding'],
    ['Deep Quiet', 'Holding'],
    ['First Run', 'Loosening'],
    ['Soft Bank', 'Loosening'],
    ['Floodwake', 'Loosening'],
    ['Reedrise', 'Opening'],
    ['Long Light', 'Opening'],
    ['Thin Water', 'Opening'],
    ['Mistreturn', 'Returning'],
    ['Dark Reed', 'Returning'],
    ['Ash Frost', 'Returning'],
  ];

  const rings = new Map(Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('[data-ring]')).map((node) => [node.dataset.ring, node]));
  const dots = new Map(Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('[data-dot]')).map((node) => [node.dataset.dot, node]));
  const reading = document.querySelector('#clock-reading');
  const centreText = document.querySelector('#clock-centre-text');
  const centreSubtext = document.querySelector('#clock-centre-subtext');

  function clamp01(value) {
    return Math.max(0, Math.min(1, value));
  }

  function fractionBetween(value, start, end) {
    return clamp01((value - start) / (end - start));
  }

  function cycleFraction(now, cycleDays, offsetDays = 0) {
    const epoch = Date.UTC(2026, 0, 1);
    const elapsedDays = (now.getTime() - epoch) / 86400000;
    return ((elapsedDays + offsetDays) / cycleDays) % 1;
  }

  function setProgress(name, progress) {
    const ring = rings.get(name);
    const dot = dots.get(name);
    const radius = RADIUS[name];
    const value = clamp01(progress);

    if (ring) {
      ring.style.strokeDashoffset = String(1 - value);
    }

    if (dot && radius) {
      const angle = value * TAU - Math.PI / 2;
      dot.setAttribute('cx', String(CENTRE + Math.cos(angle) * radius));
      dot.setAttribute('cy', String(CENTRE + Math.sin(angle) * radius));
    }
  }

  function getDayName(hour) {
    if (hour < 5) return 'deep night';
    if (hour < 8) return 'first light';
    if (hour < 12) return 'rising day';
    if (hour < 15) return 'high day';
    if (hour < 18) return 'falling light';
    if (hour < 21) return 'lampkindle';
    return 'moonrise';
  }

  function getWaterName(value) {
    if (value > 0.82) return 'twin pull';
    if (value > 0.62) return 'flood rise';
    if (value > 0.42) return 'first lift';
    if (value > 0.22) return 'moon-slack';
    return 'low-water showing';
  }

  function tick() {
    const now = new Date();
    const startOfYear = new Date(now.getFullYear(), 0, 1).getTime();
    const startOfNextYear = new Date(now.getFullYear() + 1, 0, 1).getTime();
    const yearProgress = fractionBetween(now.getTime(), startOfYear, startOfNextYear);
    const minuteProgress = (now.getMinutes() + now.getSeconds() / 60) / 60;
    const hourProgress = (now.getHours() + now.getMinutes() / 60) / 24;
    const aelun = cycleFraction(now, 29.5, 2);
    const saelith = cycleFraction(now, 71, 19);
    const water = (Math.sin(aelun * TAU) + Math.sin(saelith * TAU) + 2) / 4;
    const [vaelinyaMonth, arc] = MONTHS[now.getMonth()];
    const dayName = getDayName(now.getHours());
    const waterName = getWaterName(water);

    setProgress('year', yearProgress);
    setProgress('aelun', aelun);
    setProgress('saelith', saelith);
    setProgress('water', water);
    setProgress('hour', hourProgress);
    setProgress('minute', minuteProgress);

    const plainTime = new Intl.DateTimeFormat('en-GB', {
      hour: '2-digit',
      minute: '2-digit',
    }).format(now);

    if (centreText) centreText.textContent = arc.toUpperCase();
    if (centreSubtext) centreSubtext.textContent = plainTime;
    if (reading) {
      reading.textContent = `${dayName}. ${vaelinyaMonth}, in ${arc}. Water sign: ${waterName}.`;
    }
  }

  tick();
  window.setInterval(tick, 1000);
</script>

<style>
  .listening-clock-page {
    box-sizing: border-box;
    margin-inline: auto;
    max-width: min(1180px, calc(100vw - 2rem));
    width: 100%;
  }

  .listening-clock-page > .lede,
  .listening-clock-page > p:not(.eyebrow) {
    max-width: 58rem;
  }

  .clock-artefact {
    align-items: center;
    background:
      radial-gradient(circle at 74% 24%, rgba(255, 248, 220, 0.28), transparent 28%),
      radial-gradient(circle at 18% 82%, rgba(69, 178, 199, 0.22), transparent 32%),
      linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(35, 20, 54, 0.98), rgba(71, 48, 96, 0.95));
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 248, 220, 0.32);
    border-radius: 2rem;
    box-shadow: 0 1.5rem 4rem rgba(31, 17, 47, 0.22);
    color: #fff8dc;
    display: grid;
    gap: clamp(1.25rem, 4vw, 3rem);
    grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 0.9fr) minmax(320px, 1.1fr);
    margin: 2rem 0;
    overflow: hidden;
    padding: clamp(1.25rem, 4vw, 3rem);
    position: relative;
  }

  .clock-artefact::before {
    background:
      linear-gradient(90deg, transparent, rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1), transparent),
      repeating-linear-gradient(90deg, rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.045) 0 1px, transparent 1px 42px);
    content: '';
    inset: 0;
    opacity: 0.6;
    pointer-events: none;
    position: absolute;
  }

  .clock-copy,
  .clock-shell {
    position: relative;
    z-index: 1;
  }

  .clock-copy .eyebrow,
  .story-callout .eyebrow {
    color: rgba(255, 248, 220, 0.82);
  }

  .clock-copy h2 {
    color: #fff8dc;
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 4rem);
    letter-spacing: -0.04em;
    line-height: 0.95;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .clock-copy p {
    color: rgba(255, 248, 220, 0.88);
    font-size: 1.05rem;
  }

  .clock-reading {
    background: rgba(255, 248, 220, 0.12);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 248, 220, 0.24);
    border-radius: 1rem;
    color: #fff8dc !important;
    font-weight: 800;
    margin-top: 1.25rem;
    padding: 0.85rem 1rem;
  }

  .clock-shell {
    align-items: center;
    aspect-ratio: 1;
    display: grid;
    justify-items: center;
    margin-inline: auto;
    max-width: 560px;
    width: 100%;
  }

  .clock-halo {
    animation: listening-halo 8s ease-in-out infinite;
    background: radial-gradient(circle, rgba(255, 248, 220, 0.18), rgba(111, 199, 214, 0.13) 36%, transparent 68%);
    border-radius: 50%;
    filter: blur(0.2rem);
    grid-area: 1 / 1;
    height: 100%;
    width: 100%;
  }

  .listening-clock {
    filter: drop-shadow(0 1rem 2rem rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.28));
    grid-area: 1 / 1;
    height: auto;
    max-height: 560px;
    width: min(100%, 560px);
  }

  .clock-back-ring,
  .clock-progress {
    fill: none;
    transform: rotate(-90deg);
    transform-origin: 180px 180px;
  }

  .clock-back-ring {
    stroke: rgba(255, 248, 220, 0.13);
    stroke-width: 7;
  }

  .clock-progress {
    stroke: #fff8dc;
    stroke-dasharray: 1;
    stroke-dashoffset: 1;
    stroke-linecap: round;
    stroke-width: 7;
    transition: stroke-dashoffset 420ms linear;
  }

  .ring-year .clock-progress,
  .ring-year .clock-dot {
    stroke: #d8b6ff;
    fill: #d8b6ff;
  }

  .ring-aelun .clock-progress,
  .ring-aelun .clock-dot {
    stroke: #fff8dc;
    fill: #fff8dc;
  }

  .ring-saelith .clock-progress,
  .ring-saelith .clock-dot {
    stroke: #b8c7ff;
    fill: #b8c7ff;
  }

  .ring-water .clock-progress,
  .ring-water .clock-dot {
    stroke: #75d7e8;
    fill: #75d7e8;
  }

  .ring-hour .clock-progress,
  .ring-hour .clock-dot {
    stroke: #ffd7a6;
    fill: #ffd7a6;
  }

  .ring-minute .clock-progress,
  .ring-minute .clock-dot {
    stroke: #ffe97a;
    fill: #ffe97a;
  }

  .clock-dot {
    stroke: rgba(35, 20, 54, 0.75);
    stroke-width: 2;
  }

  .moon-dot {
    filter: drop-shadow(0 0 0.55rem rgba(255, 248, 220, 0.75));
  }

  .water-dot {
    filter: drop-shadow(0 0 0.55rem rgba(117, 215, 232, 0.7));
  }

  .clock-centre {
    fill: rgba(35, 20, 54, 0.92);
    stroke: rgba(255, 248, 220, 0.3);
    stroke-width: 2;
  }

  .clock-centre-text,
  .clock-centre-subtext {
    fill: #fff8dc;
    font-family: inherit;
    font-weight: 900;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
  }

  .clock-centre-text {
    font-size: 0.72rem;
  }

  .clock-centre-subtext {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    opacity: 0.78;
  }

  .read-clock-panel {
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  .reading-grid {
    display: grid;
    gap: 1rem;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
    margin-top: 1.25rem;
  }

  .reading-grid section {
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7);
    border: 1px solid rgba(68, 44, 88, 0.14);
    border-radius: 1.1rem;
    padding: 1rem;
  }

  .reading-grid h3 {
    color: #2b3137;
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .reading-grid p {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .story-callout {
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  @keyframes listening-halo {
    0%, 100% {
      opacity: 0.72;
      transform: scale(0.98);
    }
    50% {
      opacity: 1;
      transform: scale(1.03);
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .clock-artefact {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .clock-copy h2 {
      font-size: clamp(2.2rem, 12vw, 4rem);
    }

    .reading-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 620px) {
    .listening-clock-page {
      max-width: min(100%, calc(100vw - 1rem));
    }

    .clock-artefact {
      border-radius: 1.35rem;
      padding: 1rem;
    }

    .reading-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }

  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
    .clock-halo {
      animation: none;
    }

    .clock-progress {
      transition: none;
    }
  }
</style>
